The paper deals with computational topology algorithms for computing incidences, adjacencies, and ordering of cells in various applications such as geo-mapping, computer vision, computer graphics, finite element analysis, medical imaging, geometric design, and solid modeling. These applications are closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), graphics (cs.GR), computer vision (cs.CV), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
